(on GDZ) this is a direct copy of:
----------------------------------

cp -r UIOWA_BD_2022_FOR_RELEASE_CULLED_SPOTRF .

(on GDZ) copied the xtc code from here:
---------------------------------------

cp -r /home/aelcock/CURRENT_CODES/XTC_LIBRARY_FILE_SOURCE/XTC_IFORT/ .

you will need some environment variables set:
---------------------------------------------

need to add ifort to PATH
need to add ifort libraries to LD_LIBRARY_PATH
need to define MKLROOT

e.g. .bashrc may look like:

export PATH=$PATH:/opt/intel/compilers_and_libraries_2016.2.181/linux/bin/intel64
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:/opt/intel/compilers_and_libraries_2016.2.181/linux/compiler/lib/intel64
export MKLROOT=/opt/intel/compilers_and_libraries_2016.2.181/linux/mkl

------------------------------------------
should be able to compile everything thus:
------------------------------------------

(1) make a library file that allows us to handle .xtc files:
------------------------------------------------------------

cd XTC_IFORT
make clean
make

cp libxdrf.a ../
cd ../

(2) (if necessary) copy the appropriate mkl file for using random numbers:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

cp ${MKLROOT}/include/mkl_vsl.f90 .

(3) compile modules and then make uiowa_bd (may take a few minutes):
--------------------------------------------------------------------

ifort -c mkl_vsl.f90
ifort -c uiowa_bd.modules.f
make uiowa_bd


